e2"><![CDATA[Unlike the O.W.L.s, the W.O.M.B.A.T.s consist exclusively of written papers.  Therefore W.O.M.B.A.T.s could be sat by Muggles as well as wizards, although the Wizarding Examinations Authority does not believe that any Muggle would have the degree of inner-knowledge required to achieve a pass.The Grade 1 W.O.M.B.A.T. tested whether the examinee could exist within the magical world without falling foul of everyday wizarding laws, injuring themselves or others while using domestic spells, travelling by magical means, or by mistaking the characteristics of common magical plants and creatures. The Grade 2 W.O.M.B.A.T. is more advanced.  To pass this examination you will be required to show that you understand magical beings other than witches and wizards; that you recognise and know the use of various magical objects; that you have an awareness of wizarding current affairs, and that you have a working knowledge of the Muggle world alongside which we must live.]]></c><c n="welcometop_wombat_grade1"><![CDATA[The W.O.M.B.A.T.s, unlike the O.W.L.s, consist exclusively of written papers. Therefore W.O.M.B.A.T.s could be sat by Muggles as well as wizards, although the Wizarding Examinations Authority does not believe that any Muggle would have the degree of inner knowledge required to achieve a pass.The Grade 1 W.O.M.B.A.T. tests whether the sitter would be able to exist safely and effectively within the magical world.  Would you fall foul of Magical Law?  Would you know what to befriend/avoid in the magical Natural World?  Could you use Everyday Magic to look after yourself and your family?  And would you know how to Transport yourself within the world of wizards?This is not a straightforward Harry Potter trivia test.  While a thorough knowledge of the books is essential to achieving a good grade at W.O.M.B.A.T., you will need inspiration as well as information, applying what you know, whether by deducing the correct answer or by making intelligent guess